Definition: a toxic condition caused by ingesting or inhaling mercury
Example: acute mercury poisoning causes a metallic taste and vomiting and diarrhea and kidney problems that may lead to death
Synonyms: poisoning, a, toxic, condition, caused, by, ingesting, or, inhaling, mercury, acute, causes, metallic, taste, and, vomiting, diarrhea, kidney, problems, that, may, lead, to, death
Category: noun.state
